column2: Wearing-off symptoms during standard and extended natalizumab dosing intervals: Experiences from the COVID-19 pandemic
column6: The paper focuses on adults with multiple sclerosis (MS) receiving natalizumab, evaluating the effect of extended interval dosing (EID) compared to standard interval dosing (SID) on wearing-off symptoms. This aligns with the PICO criteria: population (adults), intervention (natalizumab, SID/EID), and outcomes (MS).
